data.name: Kraft Mozzarella
data.description: Cheese may be a foodstuff , derived from milk and produced in wide ranges of flavors, textures and forms by coagulation of the milk protein casein. It comprises proteins and fat from milk, usually the milk of cows, buffalo, goats, or sheep. During production, the milk is typically acidified and therefore the enzymes of rennet (or bacterial enzymes with similar activity) are added to cause the milk proteins (casein) to coagulate. The solids (curd) are separated from the liquid (whey) and pressed into final form. Some cheeses have aromatic molds on the rind, the outer layer, or throughout. Most cheeses melt at cooking temperature.

data.name: Horizon Organic Milk
data.description: Milk may be a nutrient-rich liquid food produced by the mammary glands of mammals. it's the first source of nutrition for young mammals, including breastfed human infants before they're ready to digest solid food. Early-lactation milk is named colostrum, which contains antibodies that strengthen the system and thus reduces the danger of the many diseases. It holds many other nutrients, including protein and lactose. Interspecies consumption of milk isn't uncommon, particularly among humans, many of whom consume the milk of other mammals.
